The wait_with_output() method returns a future that simultaneously waits for the child process to exit and collects all remaining stdout/stderr output into an Output instance. Stdin is automatically closed before waiting to prevent deadlocks. Requires piped stdout/stderr to be configured via Stdio::piped() when creating the Command.

